50|$|During World War II, most of <b>Shan</b> <b>States</b> were {{occupied}} by the Japanese. Chinese Kuomingtang (KMT) forces came down to northeastern <b>Shan</b> <b>states</b> to face the Japanese. Thai forces, allied with the Japanese, occupied Kengtung and surrounding areas in 1942, annexing the territory to the Thai state.|$|R
