25|$|However, {{this early}} {{technological}} {{advantage of the}} <b>Shan</b> <b>states</b> vis-a-vis Ava was gradually neutralized by the continued spread of the firearms. By the mid-16th century, the introduction of better firearms from Europe had reversed the positions, and helped Toungoo Dynasty annexed all of the <b>Shan</b> <b>states</b> for the first time.|$|R
50|$|In 1900, Burma was a {{province}} of British India, and {{was divided into}} two subdivisions: Lower Burma, whose capital was Rangoon with four divisions (Arakan, Irrawaddy, Pegu, Tenasserim), and Upper Burma, whose capital was Mandalay with six divisions (Meiktila, Minbu, Sagaing, North Federated <b>Shan</b> <b>States</b> and South Federated <b>Shan</b> <b>States).</b>|$|R
